article.description: Florida A&M rallies past Savannah St. 54-51
article.headline: Florida A&M rallies past Savannah St. 54-51
article.linkText: Florida A&M rallies past Savannah St. 54-51
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Jamie Adams scored 17 points and Reggie Lewis added 15, including a 3-pointer and two free throws in the final 1:07, as Florida A&M beat Savannah State 54-51 on Monday night. Terel Hall's basket gave Savannah State the lead at 31-25 with 16:19 left but the Tigers wouldn't make their next field goal until Khiry White hit a shot with 1:39 remaining. They made 12 free throws during the stretch. Florida A&M went on an 8-0 run to take a 46-43 lead with 5:14 left. Neither team would score again until Jamie Adams' free throw at the 2:13 mark. Savannah State would get within one-point on two occasions in the final minute. Jamari Bradshaw added 11 points for Florida A&M (8-14, 4-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). The Rattlers held a 54-39 advantage on the glass. Hall scored 11 for Savannah State (8-15, 6-3), while Jyles Smith added 10 and 12 rebounds.
